"Written evidence submitted by Resolution (LAI 004)Transforming Legal AidThis evidence sets out some of the issues raised by the proposed \nintroduction of a residence test for legal aid claimants in children and family cases.\nAbout Resolution Resolution, which was formerly known as the Solicitors Family Law Association (SFLA), is an organisation of 6,500 members who believe in a constructive\n, non‐confrontational approach to family law matters. Resolution also campaigns for improvements to the family justice system. \nFor further information please contact Rachel Rogers, Resolution’s Head of Policy: \nrachel.rogers@resolution.org.uk \n/ 020 3195 01\n89, or Matt Bryant, Director of Communications: \nmatt.bryant@resolution.org.uk \n/ 020 3195 0190.\n&#xa0;\nPrinciple of a residence test &#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nResidence test in family cases&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nAs well as prejudicing the parties, lack of re\npresentation is likely to impact on the timely conduct of the care proceedings.  It is unclear how some parents could be expected to provide evidence of residence in time for the crucial first hearing, or what the position of a children’s guardian with no \nability to instruct a solicitor on behalf of the child would be.\n&#xa0;\nIn our response to the \nTransforming Legal Aid\n consultation we \nasked the government for confirmation that respondents to care proceedings (which are not excluded from the residence test) will\n continue to be entitled to legal aid as now whatever their residence status - both those who are here unlawfully or beyond our borders - who are parents who can go on to take responsibility for looking after their children and maintain the children’s futu\nre within their family. \n We are hoping for specific details in the government’s response to the consultation responses when published.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIf she goes back to Pakistan she will be killed for dishonouring her family by leaving the marriage. She has been in the UK for only t\nhree months before she was assisted to flee her husband.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n3 September 2013\n"